text:
(Before It's News) John
602 approved Submitted on 2015/10/04 at 7:50 pm
Rep. Louie Gohmert is backing Daniel Webster, he says so at 2015 Values Voter Summit Speech. He also explains why he does not want the position.
He is Quote: d as saying,
“Anyway, I am supporting Dan Webster. He’s a fellow believer. He was the first Republican Speaker of the House in Florida. He’s a good man. His record’s not quite as conservative as mine, but he’s a good man. He will allow the majority to work its will, and that’s all we’re asking. That’s all we’re asking”.
https://youtu.be/ddVunxt1etQ
This transcript is from Maggie’s Notebook Blog,
http://www.maggiesnotebook.com/2015/09/louie-gohmert-spills-beans-on-boehner-fraud-deceit-corruption/#comments
Jason Chaffetz to run for Speaker. It seems to me that Daniel Webster or Louie Gohmert are a better choice. Chaffets is an establishment and did not achieve anything as a chair of the oversight committee. Ajust as Darrell Issa and others before him he was all talk, no action
